1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 1st Session of the 60th Legislature (2025)
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to public finance; prohibiting
certain government entities from entering into
8 certain non-disclosure agreements; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4601 of Title 62, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 No state or local government entity shall enter into a non-
16 disclosure agreement with any other entity as part of a settlement
17 of a claim, whether the claim is the subject of a civil lawsuit or
18 not, for money damages or other judicial relief if the settlement is
19 to be paid for with public revenue of any kind.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
